The paper deals with a new scenario in communication systems that is motivated by real-time applications, networked controlled systems, and cyber-physical systems. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Information Theory (cs.IT), and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions multimedia communication systems, which suggests that it could also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with network-utility-maximization scheduling policy, which is related to optimization problems, and thus it could also belong to the Probability (cs.PF) sub-category.
